S_n= \dfrac{1}{2} + \dfrac{1}{2\cdot 4} + \dfrac{1}{2\cdot 4 \cdot 6} +  \dfrac{1}{2\cdot 4 \cdot 6\cdots 2n}? 
t_r=\frac1{2.4.6.2r}=\frac1 {r!}\left(\frac12\right)^r
S_n=\sum_{r=1}^nt_r=\sum_{r=1}^n\frac1 {r!}\left(\frac12\right)^r
\lim_{n\to \infty}S_n=\sum_{r=1}^ \infty\frac1 {r!}(\frac12)^r=\sum_{r=0}^ \infty\frac1 {r!}(\frac12)^r-1=\text{e}^{\frac12}-1
\sqrt{\text{e}}=1.6487212707
